</ETAG>
</ENUMRECORDITEMTMPL>
<TRRECORDITEMTMPL id='_0000020D2471F1C0' oid='D29C340E5E854ea093D4DCA8DB4586BA' temploid='{99240899-F037-4d89-883E-ED655942A979}' mayBeDup='1' conv='opt'>
<NAME>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Special instruction</TUV>
</NAME>
<QUAL>SpecialInstruction</QUAL>
</TRRECORDITEMTMPL>
<TRRECORDITEMTMPL id='_0000020D2471F2C0' oid='85447423FEDC49df93F6B3565FDE55B5' temploid='C811B11E8F8F41c8BF3CFD4F459FCED4' mayBeDup='1' conv='req'>
<NAME>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Operation Cycle</TUV>
</NAME>
<DESC>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Kind of operation cycle for the event storage(e.g. power cycle, driving cycle, ...)</TUV>
</DESC>
<QUAL>DTC_OPERATION_CYCLE</QUAL>
<DEFAULT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>DEM_POWER</TUV>
</DEFAULT>
<CHOICE>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>DEM_IGNITION</TUV>
</CHOICE>
<CHOICE>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>DEM_OBD_DCY</TUV>
</CHOICE>
<CHOICE>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>DEM_WARMUP</TUV>
</CHOICE>
<CHOICE>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>DEM_POWER</TUV>
</CHOICE>
</TRRECORDITEMTMPL>
<UNSRECORDITEMTMPL id='_0000020D244B6BF0' oid='6DBAE33C310841edA23A7D79E034721C' temploid='54D97A8FFBE44911B5F6EA62EC18EBB8' mayBeDup='1' conv='opt' df='dec' v='0'>
<NAME>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Number of Trips - Active</TUV>
</NAME>
<DESC>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Number of operation cycles needed to confirm the event

The value 0 is the standard UDS behavior of confirming the event (ConfirmedDTC status bit becomes set) with the first qualified FAILED result. A value of 1 means the event becomes confirmed if it fails again in the next operation cycle.
Larger values represent confirmation in the n-th cycle e.g. 2 is confirmation in cycle after the next cycle, etc.</TUV>
</DESC>
<QUAL>NUMBER_OF_TRIPS_ACTIVE</QUAL>
</UNSRECORDITEMTMPL>
<TRRECORDITEMTMPL id='_0000020D2471D3C0' oid='E790132E88514cd6A2DD89B890D7ED23' temploid='96FDCF92905E46848F5540E1AB05AF59' mayBeDup='1' conv='opt'>
<NAME>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Enable Conditions</TUV>
</NAME>
<DESC>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>An event status report ((Pre)Failed or (Pre)Passed) will only have an effect if all EnableConditions belonging to the DTC are met at the time of report. Otherwise the result will be discarded.
Multiple C-Qualifier separated by a comma can be added here</TUV>
</DESC>
<QUAL>Enable_Conditions</QUAL>
</TRRECORDITEMTMPL>
<ENUMRECORDITEMTMPL id='_0000020D2D75C540' oid='C31C0ECF70824accA4EFC09A4ACD27B1' temploid='B8F9CF0AF6C94319A1B6BEA3DB0D2685' mayBeDup='1' conv='req' v='0' sort='id'>
<NAME>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Self Healing (Aging)</TUV>
</NAME>
<DESC>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Supported: Aging/ unlearning of the event is supported
Not Supported: Aging/ unlearning of the event is not supported</TUV>
</DESC>
<QUAL>DTC_AGING_SUPPORTED</QUAL>
<ETAG v='0'>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>supported</TUV>
</ETAG>
<ETAG v='1'>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>not supported</TUV>
</ETAG>
</ENUMRECORDITEMTMPL>
<TRRECORDITEMTMPL id='_0000020D2471D1C0' oid='00FDBEF36E6F4cce82F0813F2BF5A882' temploid='6AD0EF32419D474d9C5FCD2805DB22ED' mayBeDup='1' conv='req'>
<NAME>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Healing Cycle</TUV>
</NAME>
<QUAL>DTC_AGING_CYCLE</QUAL>
<DEFAULT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>DEM_POWER</TUV>
</DEFAULT>
<CHOICE>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>DEM_IGNITION</TUV>
</CHOICE>
<CHOICE>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>DEM_OBD_DCY</TUV>
</CHOICE>
<CHOICE>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>DEM_WARMUP</TUV>
</CHOICE>
<CHOICE>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>DEM_POWER</TUV>
</CHOICE>
</TRRECORDITEMTMPL>
<UNSRECORDITEMTMPL id='_0000020D244B88A0' oid='4CCECD64E3B14f4eB1F5335BCF14808F' temploid='DC54ED8C244C4d53BDB7B82283D8EAEC' mayBeDup='1' conv='opt' df='dec' v='0'>
<NAME>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Healing Cycles</TUV>
</NAME>
<DESC>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Cycles necessary to heal/erase event. 
Note: Activate 'Self Healing (Aging)' when using this item</TUV>
</DESC>
<QUAL>DTC_AGING_COUNTER</QUAL>
</UNSRECORDITEMTMPL>
<TRRECORDITEMTMPL id='_0000020D2471E8C0' oid='519232C4E2FD44ea86830E5BA502B7FC' temploid='2CA0107F145D487a8C308DA165E0FF06' mayBeDup='1' conv='req'>
<NAME>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Monitor Initialization Function</TUV>
</NAME>
<DESC>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Monitor initialization function is (not) required for this event</TUV>
</DESC>
<QUAL>DTC_INIT_MONITOR_REQUIRED</QUAL>
<DEFAULT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>not required</TUV>
</DEFAULT>
<CHOICE>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>required</TUV>
</CHOICE>
<CHOICE>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>not required</TUV>
</CHOICE>
</TRRECORDITEMTMPL>
<UNSRECORDITEMTMPL id='_0000020D244B6150' oid='2E3CD7C659D746299F1894EA37A61C91' temploid='B2D249520EA848fe961B1D8E08EABA93' mayBeDup='1' conv='req' df='dec' v='0'>
<NAME>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>DTC Priority</TUV>
</NAME>
<DESC>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Priority of an event, in view of full event buffer (ref. to Dem104)</TUV>
</DESC>
<QUAL>DTC_PRIORITY_VALUE</QUAL>
</UNSRECORDITEMTMPL>
<ENUMRECORDITEMTMPL id='_0000020D2D75C670' oid='37E4006330F346cb962410CB3E4A5AB1' temploid='C827388C8C574143ACBBABFBDDAE2D07' mayBeDup='1' conv='req' v='0' sort='id'>
<NAME>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>DTC Severity</TUV>
</NAME>
<DESC>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Reports the recommended action to be taken by the system (e.g. vehicle) operator</TUV>
</DESC>
<QUAL>DTC_SEVERITY_VALUE</QUAL>
<ETAG v='0'>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>noSeverity</TUV>
</ETAG>
<ETAG v='32'>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>maintenanceOnly</TUV>
</ETAG>
<ETAG v='64'>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>checkAtNextHalt</TUV>
</ETAG>
<ETAG v='128'>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>checkImmediately</TUV>
</ETAG>
</ENUMRECORDITEMTMPL>
<ENUMRECORDITEMTMPL id='_0000020D2D75C1B0' oid='3AA5DA8AEB924d3f80301B173A39B5E5' temploid='83B18212A90D4e1f82533C874ADAE8A3' mayBeDup='1' conv='req' v='1' sort='id'>
<NAME>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Pre-Debounce Algorithm</TUV>
</NAME>
<DESC>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Selects a Predebounce Algorithm</TUV>
</DESC>
<QUAL>DTC_DEBOUNCING_ALGORITHM</QUAL>
<ETAG v='0'>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Time based</TUV>
</ETAG>
<ETAG v='1'>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Counter based</TUV>
</ETAG>
</ENUMRECORDITEMTMPL>
<UNSRECORDITEMTMPL id='_0000020D244B66A0' oid='B740120A365A44c79DB40E051C6A81E4' temploid='276CB991E44F42e1896A1AEDE5B743D0' mayBeDup='1' conv='req' df='dec' v='0'>
<NAME>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Count-In step size</TUV>
</NAME>
<DESC>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Defines the Step size for incrementation (PREFAILED). Range: 0 - 127</TUV>
</DESC>
<QUAL>DTC_STEP_SIZE_PREFAILED</QUAL>
</UNSRECORDITEMTMPL>
<UNSRECORDITEMTMPL id='_0000020D244B79C0' oid='825199EAC5A8443dAD57B80099F6E7EE' temploid='8B8A36466F6347edAB800152E4E2E7EA' mayBeDup='1' conv='req' df='dec' v='0'>
<NAME>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Count-out step size</TUV>
</NAME>
<DESC>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Defines the Step size for decrementation (PREPASSED). Range 0 - 127</TUV>
</DESC>
<QUAL>DTC_STEP_SIZE_PREPASSED</QUAL>
</UNSRECORDITEMTMPL>
<ENUMRECORDITEMTMPL id='_0000020D2D75C7A0' oid='738882B88145451a9A673C9CC5DD2FF7' temploid='62E799B9AA974fab92E268C8C8A35D0D' mayBeDup='1' conv='req' v='1' sort='id'>
<NAME>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Use Jump-Up (Prefailed)</TUV>
</NAME>
<DESC>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Switch for the activation of Jump-UP:
Jump to Zero upon a change of the reported result (i.e. when after a sequence of 'prepassed' the result changes to 'prefailed')</TUV>
</DESC>
<QUAL>DTC_JUMP_UP_PREFAILED</QUAL>
<ETAG v='0'>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>No</TUV>
</ETAG>
<ETAG v='1'>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Yes</TUV>
</ETAG>
</ENUMRECORDITEMTMPL>
<ENUMRECORDITEMTMPL id='_0000020D2D75A400' oid='03C530428A194889A9FA6C963674A103' temploid='5EC926ED11B2472f9736828AE5B285B0' mayBeDup='1' conv='req' v='0' sort='id'>
<NAME>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Use Jump-Down (Prepassed)</TUV>
</NAME>
<DESC>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Switch for the activation of Jump-Down – only in combination with Jump-UP activation:
Jump to Zero upon a change of the reported result (i.e. when after a sequence of 'prefailed' the result changes to 'prepassed')</TUV>
</DESC>
<QUAL>DTC_JUMP_DOWN_PREPASSED</QUAL>
<ETAG v='0'>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>No</TUV>
</ETAG>
<ETAG v='1'>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Yes</TUV>
</ETAG>
</ENUMRECORDITEMTMPL>
<ENUMRECORDITEMTMPL id='_0000020D2D75AEB0' oid='06D211126F84430fBAB6CFEB922E8B93' temploid='210C30DD4208429fB1D4B63EC08D879E' mayBeDup='1' conv='req' v='0' sort='id'>
<NAME>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Set WarningIndicatorBit at fault</TUV>
</NAME>
<DESC>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>Yes -  the warningIndicatorRequested bit (bit 7) will be set at the same time as the confirmedDTC bit (bit 3) is set.
No - the warningIndicatorRequested bit (bit 7) is 0 at all times. </TUV>
</DESC>
<QUAL>DTC_WARNING_INDICATOR_FLAG</QUAL>
<ETAG v='0'>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>supported</TUV>
</ETAG>
<ETAG v='1'>
