<RECORD id='_0000020D3327AD30' oid='6F87974F3A854a39B28EA0338A638EA0' v='5768036'>
<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>

 1/Level_A:Abs_EmergencyBrake

 2/Level_B:STS_PCT_Fault_Pre

 3/Level_B:STS_PCT_Fault_postPSVSO

 4/Level_B:STS_PCT_Fault_PRV

 5/Level_B:STS_SCT_Fault_Pre

 6/Level_B:STS_SCT_Fault_SCT

 7/Level_B:STS_SCT_Fault_SSVSO

 8/Level_B:STS_SCT_Fault_TSVSC

 9/Level_B:STS_PSV_Fault_pre

 10/Level_B:STS_PSV_Fault_PSV

 11/Level_B:STS_PSV_Fault_PSVSC

 12/Level_B:STS_CSV_Fault_pre

 13/Level_B:STS_CSV_Fault_CSVSC

</TUV>
</TEXT>
<TRRECORDITEM idref='_0000020D2471F0C0'>
<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>1/Abs controler has detected,  that there has been no pressure increase for an implausible long time. Therefore all wheels will get pressure increase  until master cylinder pressure (driver request).
2/PCT test, when the motor advance more than 17.5mm, PSU pressure is still lower than 10bar
3/PCT detection, the PSU leakage is greater than 2cc/s and less than 5cc/s, or the normal pressure can be built after the CSV is turned off
4/PCT detection, PSU leakage greater than 5cc/s, or air volume greater than 8cc
5/SCT test, the solenoid valve did not respond
In the 6/SCT test, when the motor advances more than 17.5mm, the PSU pressure is still lower than 12bar
7/SCT test, PSU or MC2 pressure is still higher than 8bar after SSV is turned on
In the 8/SCT test, the PSU or MC2 pressure is still higher than 8bar after the TSV is turned on
9/PSV test, the solenoid valve did not respond
In the 10/SCT test, when the motor advances more than 24mm, the PSU pressure is still lower than 8bar
In 11/SCT test, after opening PSV1/2, the PSU pressure was still higher than 4bar
12/CSV test, solenoid valve did not respond
In the 13/CSV test, after opening CSV1/2, the PSU pressure was still higher than 12bar with the motor advancing, or the motor advancing speed was lower than 0.5mm/s</TUV>
</TEXT>
</TRRECORDITEM>
<TRRECORDITEM idref='_0000020D2471E7C0'>
<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>1/ The fault is rectified and can be rectified by powering on or off the device
2/ The fault is rectified and can be rectified by powering on or off the device
3/ The fault is rectified and can be rectified by powering on or off the device
4/ The fault is rectified and can be rectified by powering on or off the device
5/ The fault is rectified and can be recovered by powering on or off
6/ The fault is rectified and can be recovered by powering on or off the device
7/ The fault is rectified and can be recovered by powering on or off
8/ The fault is rectified and can be recovered by powering on or off the device
9/ The fault is rectified and can be recovered by powering on or off the device
