<RECORD id='_0000020D33278C60' oid='59A83E0DE9204d74867A893A5D6BA02B' v='5768037'>
<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>
1/Level_A:PTS 1 segment calibration is not completed
2/Level_A:PTS 2 segment calibration is not completed
3/Level_A:PTS 1 Exceeds the mechanical limit
4/Level_A:PTS 2 Exceeds the mechanical limit
5/Level_A:PTS 1 No zero calibration
6/Level_A:PTS 2 No zero calibration
7/Level_A:PTS 1SCN reports an internal fault
8/Level_A:PTS 2SCN reports an internal fault
9/Level_A:PTS 1SCN reports an internal fault
10/Level_A:PTS 2SCN reports an internal fault
11/Level_A:PTS 1SENT data is not trusted
12/Level_A:PTS 2SENT data is not trusted
13/Level_A:PTS 1 Calibration data is incomplete
14/Level_A:PTS 2 Calibration data is incomplete
15/Level_A:Pts2Asic Signal loss
16/Level_A:Pts1Asic Signal loss
</TUV>
</TEXT>
<TRRECORDITEM idref='_0000020D2471F0C0'>
<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>The 1/PTS1 segment is calibrated with the significant digit not set to 1
The significant digit of 2/PTS2 is not set to 1
3/PTS after calibration, the travel value exceeds the mechanical limit, i.e. -1.5mm to 43.5mm.
4/PTS after calibration, the travel value exceeds the mechanical limit, i.e. -1.5mm to 43.5mm.
5/PTS Zero calibration not completed
6/PTS Zero calibration not completed
7/PTS 1SCN reported an internal fault, repeated more than 5 times
8/PTS 2SCN reports an internal fault, repeated more than 5 times
9/PTS 1SCN reports an external circuit failure, repeated more than 5 times
10/PTS 2SCN reports an external circuit failure, repeated more than 5 times
11/PTS 1SENT data is not within the limit, repeated more than five times
12/PTS 2SENT data is not within the limit, repeated more than five times
13/PTS 1 segment calibration data were missing and mature for 1 time
14/PTS 2 segment calibration data were missing and matured once
15/ Signal is lost, timestamp stops updating, and 5 5ms tasks (25ms) are reported continuously
16/ The signal is lost, the timestamp stops updating, and is reported for 5 5ms tasks (25ms)</TUV>
</TEXT>
</TRRECORDITEM>
<TRRECORDITEM idref='_0000020D2471E7C0'>
<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>1/ Perform segment calibration, and restore after re-powering
2/ Perform segment calibration, and restore after re-powering
3/ Check hardware status or re-zero calibration. Once the fault is rectified
4/ Check hardware status or re-zero calibration. Once the fault is rectified
5/ After zero calibration, the fault is eliminated once
6/ After zero calibration, the fault is eliminated once
7/ One recovery
8/ One recovery
9/ One recovery
10/ One recovery
11/ One recovery
12/ One recovery
13/ Recovery after re-segment calibration
14/ Recovery after re-segment calibration
15/ The signal is restored, the timestamp begins to update, and the fault is eliminated for 5 5ms tasks (25ms)
16/ The signal is restored, the timestamp begins to update, and the fault is eliminated for 5 5ms tasks (25ms)</TUV>
</TEXT>
</TRRECORDITEM>
