<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>
1/Level_A:PS_2 indicates that the temperature exceeds the threshold
</TUV>
</TEXT>
<TRRECORDITEM idref='_0000020D2471F0C0'>
<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>1/PS_2 reports low temperature. If the output voltage of Vtemp is greater than 90% of Vbat, the temperature is lower than -42 ° C. The fault reached maturity for 10 times.</TUV>
</TEXT>
</TRRECORDITEM>
<TRRECORDITEM idref='_0000020D2471E7C0'>
<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>1/ once eliminated</TUV>
