<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>

 1/Level_B:Axs_Plaus &#38; Axs_PlausHighAccel

</TUV>
</TEXT>
<TRRECORDITEM idref='_0000020D2471F0C0'>
<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>1/The failure is set if the difference between measured longitudinal acceleration and longitudinal acceleration calculated by differentiating vehicle velocity is higher than a velocity depending threshold {%default: 3.5 m/s? (P_AxsHighAccelerationMonitoringThreshold)%}. &#38; The failure is set if the longitudinal acceleration is higher than a minimum threshold {%default: 0.5 m/s? (P_AxsHighAccelerationAddThreshold)%} added by a threshold depending on velocity  {%default: 3.5 m/s? (P_AxsHighAccelerationMonitoringThreshold)%} for a long time during driving.</TUV>
</TEXT>
</TRRECORDITEM>
<TRRECORDITEM idref='_0000020D2471E7C0'>
<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>1/ The fault is rectified and can be rectified by powering on or off the device</TUV>
</TEXT>
</TRRECORDITEM>
<ENUMRECORDITEM idref='_0000020D2D75B830' v='1'/>
<TRRECORDITEM idref='_0000020D2471F2C0'>
