<TRRECORDITEM idref='_0000020D2471F0C0'>
<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>1/Voos below 2.3V or above 2.7V, debounce 20ms
2/A4911 Faults Exist or a latch fault is detected or output is disabled. debounce 15ms
3/SPI frame If the communication fails for five consecutive frames, the fault becomes mature
4/A4911 VBRG higher than VBB-8V
5/A4911 Self-test, phase A cannot be monitored normally
6/A4911 Self-test, B phase phase cannot be monitored normally
7/A4911 Self-test, C phase phase cannot be monitored normally
8/A4911 U phase current sampling open
9/A4911 V phase current sampling open
10/A4911 W phase current sampling open
11/A4911 LSSA higher than 5V(4.5-5.5V)
12/A4911 LSSB above 5V(4.5-5.5V)
13/A4911 LSSC above 5V(4.5-5.5V)
14/ Power-on self-test to complete the fault test, the chip actively triggered
The VREG undervoltage or overvoltage self-test fails
15/Power-on self-test Completes the fault test, and the chip actively triggers
YRU = 1 command, no VREG undervoltage fault is detected
16/ Power-on self-test To complete the fault test, the chip actively triggered
The YRO = 1 command indicates that no VREG overvoltage fault is detected
17/ Power-on self-test Completes the fault test, and the chip actively triggers
YTW = 1 command, no high temperature warning fault is detected
18/ Power-on self-test Complete the fault test, the chip actively triggered
If YOT = 1, no overtemperature fault is detected
19/ Power-on self-test Completes the fault test, and the chip actively triggers
VBB undervoltage or overvoltage self-test failed
20/ Power-on self-test to complete the fault test, the chip actively triggered
Command YSO = 1. No VBB overvoltage fault is detected
21/ Power-on self-test Complete the fault test, the chip actively triggered
The YSU = 1 command indicates that the VBB undervoltage fault is not detected
22/ Power-on self-test to complete the fault test, the chip actively triggered
If the YGU = 1 command is used, the MOS VGS undervoltage self-check on AH, AL, BH, BL, CH, and CL fails
23/ Power-on self-test Complete the fault test, the chip actively triggered
If the command YGU = 1 is used, the MOS VGS undervoltage fault on the AL terminal is not detected
24/ Power-on self-test to complete the fault test, the chip actively triggered
If the YGU = 1 command is run, the MOS VGS undervoltage fault on AH is not detected
25/ Power-on self-test To complete the fault test, the chip actively triggered
If the YGU = 1 command is used, the MOS VGS undervoltage fault on the BL terminal is not detected
26/ Power-on self-test to complete the fault test, the chip actively triggered
Command YGU = 1. The MOS VGS undervoltage fault on BH is not detected
27/ Power-on self-test Complete the fault test, the chip actively triggers
The YGU = 1 command indicates that the MOS VGS undervoltage fault of CL terminal is not detected
