<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>
1/Level_B: The three-phase feedback current and the command current are incorrect
2/Level_B: The three-phase sampling error occurs
3/Level_B: The current and bias current are incorrectly sampled
4/Level_B: indicates that the current overflows
5/Level_B: The current is out of control
6/Level_A: indicates an overcurrent error
7/Level_A: indicates an overcurrent error
8/Level_A: indicates an overcurrent error
</TUV>
</TEXT>
<TRRECORDITEM idref='_0000020D2471F0C0'>
<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>1/IaIbIcref&#62; Threshold and IaIbIcfbk&#60; Threshold, specify the threshold size
2/Iqref unit difference &#60; threshold and Iq unit difference &#62; threshold
The difference between Id and Idref + the difference between Iq and Iqref &#62; threshold, and the threshold size is defined
3/ current and bias current sampling adc over the maximum and minimum range to refine the diagnostic strategy
4/ When any three-phase current overcurrent fault occurs
5/ The actual current Iq is less than the target Iq current 25A
6/ The fault is rectified and can be recovered by powering on or off the device
7/ The fault is rectified and can be recovered by powering on or off
8/ The fault is rectified and can be recovered by powering on or off the device</TUV>
</TEXT>
</TRRECORDITEM>
<TRRECORDITEM idref='_0000020D2471E7C0'>
<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>1/ The fault is rectified and can be rectified by powering on or off the device
2/ The fault is rectified and can be rectified by powering on or off the device
3/ The fault is rectified and can be rectified by powering on or off the device
4/ The fault is rectified and can be rectified by powering on or off the device
5/ The fault is rectified and can be recovered by powering on or off
6/ The fault is rectified and can be recovered by powering on or off the device
7/ The fault is rectified and can be recovered by powering on or off
8/ The fault is rectified and can be recovered by powering on or off the device</TUV>
</TEXT>
</TRRECORDITEM>
