<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>

 1/Level_B:STF_HardCircuit

 2/Level_B:STF_SoftCircuit1

 3/Level_B:STF_SoftCircuit2

</TUV>
</TEXT>
<TRRECORDITEM idref='_0000020D2471F0C0'>
<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>1/Pressure sensor signal not plausible (too high) compared to plunger position.A Hard Circuit failure occurs if the pressure sensor shows higher values than expected w.r.t. the plunger position. pV-data of vehicle is used for plausibilization.
 2/A Soft Circuit 1 failure occurs if the pressure sensor shows lower values than expected w.r.t. the plunger position. pV-data of vehicle is used for plausibilization.
 3/A Soft Circuit 2 failure occurs if the pressure sensor shows lower values than expected w.r.t. the plunger position. pV-data of vehicle is used for plausibilization.</TUV>
</TEXT>
</TRRECORDITEM>
<TRRECORDITEM idref='_0000020D2471E7C0'>
<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>1/ The fault is rectified and can be rectified by powering on or off the device
2/ The fault is rectified and can be rectified by powering on or off the device
3/ The fault is rectified and can be rectified by powering on or off the device</TUV>
</TEXT>
</TRRECORDITEM>
