<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>

 1/Level_A:CANTrcv1 operating mode Fault
 2/Level_A:CANTrcv1 CAN Communicaiton mode Fault

 3/Level_A:CANTrcv1 Overheating Warning
 4/Level_A:CANTrcv1 Wakeup Event Cluster Flag Issue
 5/Level_A:CANTrcv1 WAKE_pin Abnormal Wakeup
 6/Level_A:CANTrcv1System  Wakeup
 7/Level_A:CANTrcv1 SPI failure

 8/Level_A:CANTrcv1 overtemperature

 9/Level_A:CANTrcv2 operating modes Fault
 10/Level_A:CANTrcv2 CAN operating modes Fault
 11/Level_A:CANTrcv2 Overheating Warning
 12/Level_A:CANTrcv2 Wakeup Event Cluster Flag Issue
 13/Level_A:CANTrcv2 WAKE_pin Abnormal Wakeup
 14/Level_A:CANTrcv2System_event  Wakeup
 15/Level_A:CANTrcv2 SPI failure

 16/Level_A:CANTrcv2 overtemperature

</TUV>
</TEXT>
<TRRECORDITEM idref='_0000020D2471F0C0'>
<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>1/Trcv chip internal working mode is not consistent with the expected working mode of the software, one failure is mature
2/Trcv chip communication state is inconsistent with the expected communication state of the software, and the fault is mature if it is not successful for 1 time
3/ The temperature exceeds 147℃, (1 debounce) mature.
4/ An internal chip fault causes an abnormal wake event detection (1 debounce)
5/ The system detects a WAKE_pin wakeup (the wake_PIN wakeup source is shielded by the system design), once mature
6/ Trcv wakes up abnormally due to internal system faults such as SPI failure and overtemperature failure
7/ Chip detects SPI communication failure, once mature.
8/ Once mature at temperatures above 177 ° C
9/Trcv chip internal working mode is not consistent with the expected working mode of the software, one failure is mature
10/Trcv chip communication state is not consistent with the expected communication state of the software, and the fault is mature if it is unsuccessful for 1 time
11/ The temperature exceeds 147℃, (1 debounce) mature.
12/ An internal chip fault causes an abnormal wake event detection (1 debounce)
13/ The system detects a wake-up via WAKE_pin (the wake source is shielded by the system design), once mature
14/ Trcv wakes up abnormally due to internal system faults such as SPI failure and overtemperature failure
15/ Chip detects SPI communication failure, once mature.
16/ Once mature at temperatures above 177 ° C</TUV>
</TEXT>
</TRRECORDITEM>
<TRRECORDITEM idref='_0000020D2471E7C0'>
<TEXT>
<TUV xml:lang='en-US'>1/ once eliminated
2/ Eliminate once
